Did not make it very far in the game. I got to irritated by the controls. Walking is a pain in the butt, and sometimes it just wouldn't pick up on the right input. I would try to walk and it would just lift a leg and never move even while leaning forward. Im gonna pass on this game.
I like it! I like it a lot! Even though it's a heavily "borrowed" star war game, still one of the kind tbat I've played so far, on mobile anyway.
Please add the option to change button size. I play on a large tablet, and I am tired of taking damage due missing a button half the size of my thumb.

I would've rated 5 stars, if it wasn't for the last chapters of the game, (IV, V, & VI). I feel like the devs half-assed the ending, because no matter which side you pick, "Thuuagii or Mankind," in chapter IV, your choice doesn't matter! The outcome remains the same, and the only thing that SLIGHTLY changes is the dialogue. IMO, each ending sucked DICK, and I am incredibly dissatisfied with both! Spoiler alert: Everyone dies, including yourself! And we are all left on a MASSIVE cliffhanger...

It seems to have a difficulty spike and I have trouble getting past levels. After you choose your side, the grenade launcher becomes almost useless. The only idea is that the grenades can be used in minefields to trigger the bombs.

Definitely a difficult game that's why I played on easy it's more fun because I'm not a mad man. The game play and graphics are very cool and entertaining. It's very satisfying building a super powerful Walker no one can stand a chance. But what kills it for me is these missions that push the controls to the limit and you have to avoid stepping on people or later landmines that you have no proper way of knowing are there . But the endings without spoiling anything are the damn same it felt lazy

While it was a very nice story and gameplay was very smooth, re-playability of the game is obsolete. After working so hard to unlock so much for your Walker there's nothing after the end. With a story that can be beat in 45+ minutes, It would be nice to see a mode where you can do endless random missions offering an array of different challenges, $4.99 plus tax is not truly worth the price for what you get

It's alot of fun addicting to just sad to see it end so soon it would be nice to see another story or a sandbox added were like endless mode or survive as long as you can add drops for oxygen refill and repair bots

OK the game overall is pretty bad and fun.One the game with ability to step on the enemies is fun but if u accidently step on a friendly u got to start over the Entire mission and its annoying please add check points on the missions were u have to deliver supplies and on the landmines missions.Two the black visalusier on the missions should have an option to remove it cause it just blocks the view for the player and hard missions. Also could u add customization to the Walker like paints jobs.

Really fun game. Only problem I had with it is that when I try to knock over the natives with the walkers legs, they just bounce off like a ball.

This game is definitely different. I see lots of complaints about the controls but I think it's pretty cool. You have a lot more control over the mech rather than just moving a joystick-.-, you have to move each foot independently. I enjoy the manual controls over a mech, makes me feel more like a pilot lol. But it's definitely not for everyone, especially if you like joystick controls -.-
Good game art style is also very good

Good game Overall a fantastic game, worth $5. The only problems I have with the game is the repetitive side quests and the HORRIBLY SHOVED IN ENDING. Other than that I found everything else in the game to be pretty fun and engaging !SPOILER ALERT! I was really hoping to see what would happen and what all of my choices and hours of gameplay led up to but instead all you get to see is you looking around and then suffocating to death, really disapointing. Still a fantastic game for its price.

Absolutely horrible controls. After about three missions my thumbs start hurting for having to constantly manually control the legs of the Walker. Weapons are trash beyond belief, walking over enemies seems like the only way to fight larger groups. And then when you get a mission where you have to avoid stepping on friendlies the game becomes unplayable. Bunch of suicidal lemmings that hide behind visual obstructions so you can't even tell if your stepping on them or not.

Game is alright but could be better. Missions feel like too much work compared to the reward. Fixing your mech after each mission costs 1/3 of what you're paid. The walking mechanics is ok, takes some time to get used to but the weapon firing is a bit annoying. Your guns take longer to cooldown then what it takes to use them. Especially when you're firing and the aim keeps switching lanes missing majority of the enemies since they were all on one side. Takes the fun out of the game.
